          </div><div class="txt commenttxt">A vegetarian making these?  That must be true love! :)<br>Yes, the white-ish part is the fat.   The grease just naturally comes off from the bacon as it cooks. You don't need to do anything to the pan (except drill/poke holes in the bottom)</div><div id="files"><a name="files"></a></div><div id="commentactioncontainer_CGTHB0QGYGGN74A" class="comment-actions"><div style="float:right;"><a id="replytolink_CGTHB0QGYGGN74A" class="med-button replylink commentloop_a_5" href="#" onclick="return false;"><b>Reply</b></a></div><div class="commentloop_div_4 mt5"></div></div></div><a name="CSPYF9MGYKQ5IX9"></a><div class="comment entryList clearfix  " style="margin-left:20px;"><div class="comment-authorpic"><a href="/member/ErinMichelle/"><img src="http://img.instructables.com/files/deriv/F88/D90H/GYLDEKHT/F88D90HGYLDEKHT.TINY.jpg" alt="" /></a></div><div class="comment-info"><span>Feb 13, 2012. 10:11 AM</span><a href="/member/ErinMichelle/" class="entryListTitle" style="line-height:16px;padding-right:4px;padding-left:0px;">ErinMichelle</a>
