          </div><div class="txt commenttxt">Oh, and I just a hammer and nail to make the hole in the bottom of the muffin tin.  It worked well, and made a nice curved bottom so that grease did not pool much at all. </div><div id="files"><a name="files"></a></div><div id="commentactioncontainer_CQ4287SGO5IG5GZ" class="comment-actions"><div style="float:right;"><a id="replytolink_CQ4287SGO5IG5GZ" class="med-button replylink commentloop_a_5" href="#" onclick="return false;"><b>Reply</b></a></div><div class="commentloop_div_4 mt5"></div></div></div><a name="CGXUOQXGMIG0IXS"></a><div class="comment entryList clearfix toplevel " style="margin-left:0px;"><div class="comment-authorpic"><a href="/member/kaikudo/"><img src="http://img.instructables.com/files/deriv/F8N/Y77W/FYIZ3ZZ2/F8NY77WFYIZ3ZZ2.TINY.jpg" alt="" /></a></div><div class="comment-info"><span>Apr 18, 2011. 4:10 AM</span><a href="/member/kaikudo/" class="entryListTitle" style="line-height:16px;padding-right:4px;padding-left:0px;">kaikudo</a>
